  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to block users so that I can manage spammers.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nLately Status has seen a bunch of spam by users that post the same message in lots of channels such as:\r\n\r\n> I've had a big failure in my investment.\r\n> If you give me a bit of ETH I will surely succeed and pay you back twice.\r\n> 0x3439c7d08463df4e2724ecdcf295a5a9f9fc54d1\r\n\r\nor\r\n\r\n> 0x62cede580c1e5900e4871c26ace86fb5ae15949c\r\n> ETH please\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nCan block users, and then not see their messages\r\n\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\nThese type of messages can gunk up the status chat, so one way of dealing with this type of spam could be to block users and hide their messages.\r\n\r\nThis should work on both mobile and desktop.\r\n\r\nSpam mitigation and prevention will have many approaches, but blocking users is just one small step.",
