    "body": "As discuss during our weekly chat meeting I want to open here the discussion on hard vs soft block. I think we can do the two separately if we have a clear semantic distinction.\r\n\r\n# Hard block (aka permaban)\r\n\r\n- no unblocking (at least for now)\r\n- all messages from the user are deleted\r\n- all future messages are ignored\r\n- the quickest and easiest to implement: permabanned user are completely removed from contacts, stored aside as a list of blocked public-keys. Ignoring can be done on status-react side for now and later by status-go which could maintain the list of ignored public-keys in the future since there is already persistence for group-chats.\r\n\r\n# Soft block (aka ignore)\r\n\r\n- same feature familly as metadata I want to add to contacts, chats and messages\r\n- when a user is marked as ignored, the metadata tag `ignored` is added to it's contact entry in the database. All his message are hidden in the UI, not counted in the unread counter, not shown in the last message of chats (these requirements are important, because right now it cannot be done in a straightforward way and requires lots of changes)\r\n- a user can be `unignored` and all his messages are shown and counted again",
